# Copy variable NAMES that match YOUR bundler into YOUR app’s .env (not into the apexstream package).
# The SDK does not read files — you pass url + apiKey in code (see docs/sdk-configuration.md).
#
# WebSocket URL must end with /v1/ws (one slash, not //v1/ws). Examples:
#   ws://127.0.0.1:8081/v1/ws
#   ws://YOUR_SERVER_IP:30081/v1/ws   (k8s NodePort)
#   wss://your-domain.example/v1/ws
#
# --- Vite ---
# VITE_APEXSTREAM_WS_URL=wss://your-domain.example/v1/ws
# VITE_APEXSTREAM_API_KEY=
# Local dev (http:// + ws:// to LAN / NodePort): optional explicit flag (see packages/client README)
# VITE_APEXSTREAM_ALLOW_INSECURE=1
# In code: allowInsecureTransport = wsUrl.startsWith("ws://") || VITE_APEXSTREAM_ALLOW_INSECURE === "1"|"true"
#
# --- Create React App ---
# REACT_APP_APEXSTREAM_WS_URL=wss://your-domain.example/v1/ws
# REACT_APP_APEXSTREAM_API_KEY=
#
# --- Next.js (client) ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APEXSTREAM_WS_URL=wss://your-domain.example/v1/ws
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APEXSTREAM_API_KEY=
#
# --- Node / scripts ---
# APEXSTREAM_WS_URL=ws://127.0.0.1:8081/v1/ws
# APEXSTREAM_API_KEY=
# APEXSTREAM_ALLOW_INSECURE_TRANSPORT=1   # optional; or derive from ws:// URL (see README)
